message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Norway in the past 5 years was the terrorist attack on July 22, 2011. A right-wing extremist named Anders Behring Breivik carried out a bombing in Oslo, targeting government buildings, and later went on a shooting spree at a youth camp on the island of Utøya. This tragic event resulted in the deaths of 77 people, mostly teenagers, and left a lasting impact on the country.
